<PRE>
                                       THE WHITE HOUSE
                                OFFICE OF THE VICE PRESIDENT
 For Immediate Release                                              December 5, 1995


                      U.S.-SOUTH AFRICA BINATIONAL COMMISSION
                                AGRICULTURE COMMITTEE


     At the meeting of the US-SA BNC today, Vice President Al Gore and South African
Deputy President Thabo Mbeki announced the establishment of an Agriculture Committee to
be co-chaired by the U.S. Secretary of Agriculture Daniel Glickman and South African
Minister of Agriculture Andre Ivan van Niekerk.

     &quot;I fully endorse the establishment of an agriculture committee under the U.s.-South
Africa Binational Commission,&quot; said Vice President Al Gore.  &quot;This committee will play an
important role in strengthening U.S.-South Africa relations in the area of agriculture by
facilitating successful agricultural linkages between our two nations.

     The Agriculture Committee will provide a forum to facilitate mutual discussion,
cooperation, and initiatives in the areas of agricultural trade, investment, and development;
rural economic and community development; marketing, regulation, and safety of food
products; food and nutrition; natural resources; and agricultural economics, extension, and
research.

     The Agriculture Committee will complement the five standing committees already
under the auspices of the Commission - Trade and Investment, Human Resources
Development and Education, Energy Development, Science and Technology, Conservation,
Environment, and Water.
</PRE></BODY></HTML>
