<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>USIA: U.S. Policy in the Gulf -- UN
Resolutions pertaining to Iraq</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="unlogo1.gif">
<B><H2>United Nations Resolutions<br>
Pertaining to Iraq and Sanctions</H2></B><P>
<hr></CENTER> 
The United States has always acted in concert and in accordance
with United Nations Security Council Resolutions in matters
pertinent to Iraq's invasion of Kuwait, Desert Storm, and the
subsequent sanctions imposed upon Iraq.
<P>
A list of relevant United Nations Security Council Resolutions is
listed here.
<P><ul>
<LI><A HREF="unsc986.htm">UNSC 986</A> Authorizing the Sale of
Oil for Food/Humanitarian Relief. April 14, 1995 
<LI><A HREF="unsc686.htm">UNSC 686</A> Establishing Post-War
Cease-Fire Terms. March 2, 1995 
<LI><A HREF="unsc678.htm">UNSC 678</A> Authorizing Use of "All
Necessary Means" to Liberate Kuwait. November 29, 1990 
<LI><A HREF="unsc660.htm">UNSC 660</A> Condemning the Iraqi
Invasion of Kuwait. August 2, 1990 
</ul>
