<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>USA-RSA - Development Working Group</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000">
<H2>USA-RSA BINATIONAL COMMISSION AGRICULTURE COMMITTEE
INSTITUTIONAL AND HUMAN RESOURCE DEVELOPMENT WORKING GROUP TERMS
OF REFERENCE</H2>
<P>PREAMBLE</P>
<P>1. The establishment of a Working Group under the Agriculture
Committee is recognized;  </P>
<P>2. Such a Working Group will constitute a forum to facilitate
discussions and cooperation on institutional development;</P>
<P>3. That discussions and cooperation to the above will be
conducted with due recognition of  the development level and
structural differences of the agricultural sectors of the USA and
the RSA;</P>
<P>4. And that discussions and cooperation to the above will be
conducted with due recognition of and in collaboration with other
Working Groups, under the Agriculture Committee and within the
Binational Commission.</P>
<P>ARTICLE 1</P>
<P>PURPOSE</P>
<P>1. To facilitate the exchange of technical information and
the training of public and private personnel in the technical,
business, managerial, and organizational areas.</P>
<P>2. To initiate cooperative ventures.</P>
<P>ARTICLE 2</P>
<P>CONTENT AND ISSUES</P>
<P>1. Facilitate the Development of Human and Institutional
Capacity for Policy Making and Knowledge Generation and
Dissemination with focus on issues which include the following:</P>
<P><BR>?  train and retrain officers in policy, technical and
scientific occupational areas;
<BR>?  hold Workshops and Conferences and have lectures on
topical issues and latest advances;
<BR>?  facilitate exposure visits and exchanges for officers
between provinces within the country and abroad;
<BR>?  resource management; and
<BR>?  secondary, vocational and/or higher education in the food
and agricultural
<BR>?  curriculum development
<BR>?  faculty training
<BR>?  faculty exchange
<BR>?  university linkage
</P>
<P>2. Facilitate the Development of Agriculture and Agribusiness
 Organizations with focus on issues which include the following:</P>
<P>?  farmer unions;
<BR>?  farmer associations;
<BR>?  farmer cooperatives;
<BR>?  agribusiness management;
<BR>?  farmer's commodity bodies;
<BR>?  farmer lobbies; and
<BR>?  development of rural financial institutions.
</P>
<P>3. Farm, Agribusiness and Entreprenurial Development with
focus on issues which include the following:</P>
<P>?  entrance into farming and agribusiness and starting a 
business for family needs or for wider market needs;
<BR>?  empower prospective farmers and entrepreneurs with
business and managerial skills and knowledge;
<BR>?  enable prospective farmers and entrepreneurs to exploit
existing and new markets opportunities;
<BR>?  assist prospective farmers and entrepreneurs to start
business contacts in and outside South Africa; and
<BR>?  help link prospective farmers and entrepreneurs with
indigenous research, technological and advisory institutions.
</P>
<P>4. To assist in the Development of Off- and On-Farm Human and
Institutional Infrastructure with focus on issues which include
the following:</P>
<P>?  secure and transferable land tenure;
<BR>?  feeder roads and telecommunication;
<BR>?  water-harvesting techniques and reservoirs;
<BR>?  markets and marketing stalls; and
<BR>?  farmer service centres.
</P>
<P>5. Public Service Human Resource Development with focus on
issues which include the following:</P>
<P>?  train and retrain officers in managerial, administrative,
advisory, technical and scientific occupational areas;
<BR>?  hold Workshops and Conferences and have lectures on
topical issues andlatest advances;
<BR>?  facilitate exposure visits and exchanges for officers
between provinceswithin the country and abroad.
</P>
<P>_________________________________________________  Date:
_____________________ Masiphula Mbongwa</P>
<P>Chief Director, Programmes and Information,</P>
<P>South African National Department of Agriculture</P>
<P>_________________________________________________  Date:
_____________________ B. H. Robinson</P>
<P>Administrator, Cooperative State Research, Education and
Extension Service U.S. Department of Agriculture</P></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
