<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>USIA: U.S. Policy in Iraq -- Dept. of State
Statement</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff><IMG SRC="usis2.jpg">
<CENTER><B><H2>Statement of the Department of State<br>
On U.S. Participation in UNSCR 986</H2>
<br>by Spokeman Nicholas Burns, June 5, 1996</B><P>
<IMG SRC="footer.gif"></CENTER> 
<p>
Washington -- The U.S. administration has decided to permit
American companies to participate in transactions under the
United Nations Security Council Iraq "oil-for-food" arrangement,
UNSC Resolution 986.
<P>
Following is the official text of a June 5 statement by State
Department spokesman Nicholas Burns:
<P>
(Begin official text)
<P>
The Administration has decided to allow American companies to
participate in transactions involving Iraq under UN Security
Council Resolution 986. Our decision permits U.S. companies to
buy or sell goods or services, including oil and humanitarian
supplies, to the extent permitted by the UN Resolution and the
extent permitted by the UN Sanctions
Committee.
<P>
Resolution 986 is the so-called "oil for food" arrangement that
Iraq recently agreed to implement under strict UN supervision. It
is a humanitarian exception to the UN economic embargo against
Iraq and does not represent a lifting of the sanctions. The
proceeds from oil sales are to compensate the victims of Iraqi
aggression and to purchase humanitarian supplies.
<P>
Oil revenues will be tightly controlled to insure they benefit
the Iraqi population and to prevent abuse. All aspects of 986
will require case-by-case approval and will be strictly monitored
by the United Nations. All oil revenue will be deposited in an
escrow account established by and under the control of the UN.
The Administration has decided that it is appropriate to allow
U.S. commercial participation in 986 transactions in these
circumstances. Any U.S. firm that wishes to participate in such
transactions with Iraq under 986 must be licensed by the U.S.
treasury Department, Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC).
<P>
(End official text)  
<HR>
<center>This Web site was produced and is maintained by the
United States Information Agency.<P><A HREF="gulfmain.htm">
Return</A> to the Gulf Security Homepage <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE
SRC="usisflag.gif"> <A HREF="http://www.usia.gov/usis.html">
Return</A> to the USIS homepage 
</CENTER></body></html>

