<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Binational Fulbrigth Commission</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">
<H3 ALIGN="center">Monday November 18, 1996<BR>    JOINT
DECLARATION OF INTENT BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES INFORMATION
AGENCY  OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA  AND THE MINISTRY OF
EDUCATION OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA  ON  STUDYING THE 
ESTABLISHMENT OF A BINATIONAL FULBRIGHT COMMISSION</H3>
<P>
 The United States Information Agency of the United States of
America and the Ministry of Education of the Republic of South
Africa, hereinafter referred to as the &quot;Participants,&quot; 
</P>
<P>
Having an interest in cooperating in the area of academic and
professional exchanges; 
</P>
<P>
Having an interest in promoting the sharing of information and
expertise in a variety of fields, but especially the humanities
and social sciences;  
</P>
<P>
Having an interest in promoting mutual understanding between the
people of the United States of America and the people of  the
Republic of South Africa;  
</P>
<P>
Having an interest in maximizing monies spent on exchanges and
keeping administrative expenses to the minimum necessary for
effective management; 
</P>
<P>
Noting that human resources of both countries can be developed
through exposure to foreign cultures, ideas, and methods of
operation, and that innovative concepts and programs can result
from such exchanges; 
</P>
<P>
Hereby declare their intentions as follows: 
</P>
<P>
1.  	The Participants intend to create a Joint Working Group to
investigate establishing a binational Fulbright Commission that
would supervise the bilateral academic and professional exchanges
funded by the United States Information Agency and the Ministry
of Education, as well as whatever private funding can be
generated.  This intended joint exploration may include, but is
not limited to, the following:  		A) 	Appointing an equal number
of persons to represent each of the Participants on the Joint
Working Group;  		B)	Communications with individuals and
organizations familiar with existing Fulbright commissions, the
commission concept, and its implementation;  		C)	Undertaking
exploratory travel to consult with officials of existing
commissions in appropriate countries;  		D)	Considering the
administrative structure, government and private funding, and
composition of the Board members;  		E)	Submitting final written
recommendations on their findings to the Participants no later
than April 30, 1996, or another date mutually agreed upon by the
Participants. 
</P>
<P>
2.	The United States Information Service in South Africa and  the
Ministry of Education of the Republic of South Africa will
jointly coordinate the activities contemplated by this Joint
Declaration of Intent. 
</P>
<P>
3.	The Participants will submit the final recommendations of the
Joint Working Group as well as their own evaluation of those
recommendations to their respective governments no later than May
30, 1996, or another date mutually agreed upon by the
Participants. 
</P>
<P>
4. 	All costs associated with the cooperation contemplated
herein, including payment of salaries, travel and subsistence
expenses of personnel participating on or cooperating with the
Joint Working Group will be borne by the country of origin of the
personnel unless otherwise determined by the Participants.   
</P>
<P>
Signed, in duplicate, at Pretoria, Republic of South Africa, this
4th day of December 1995.  
</P>
<P>
FOR THE						FOR THE UNITED STATES INFORMATION		MINISTRY OF
EDUCATION OF THE AGENCY OF THE UNITED			REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA:
STATES OF AMERICA:
</P>
<P>
     JOSEPH DUFFEY				   	SIBUSISO BENGU DIRECTOR, UNITED
STATES		   	MINISTER OF EDUCATION INFORMATION AGENCY
<!-- BEGIN BODY FOOTER SECTION --></P></BODY></HTML>
