<HEAD>
<TITLE>inaugural announcement</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#AA0000" VLINK="#008800" ALINK="#008800">
<PRE>

                       THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
                                  AND OF
                       THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
                               TO ESTABLISH
                THE U.S.-SOUTH AFRICA BINATIONAL COMMISSION


The governments of the United States of America and of the Republic of South Africa hereby
establish a binational commission for the purpose of facilitating bilateral cooperation on key
issues of mutual concern.  To this end, the Governments have reached an understanding
regarding the Commission as follows:

-- The Commission will be co-chaired by the Vice President of the United States of America
and the Deputy President of the Republic of South Africa.  Each Government will appoint a
senior-level vice-chairperson.

-- The Commission will consist of five committees, specifically on business development;
environment, conservation and sustainable development; sustainable energy development;
human resource development and education; and science and technology.  Other committees
may be established as mutually agreed.  The committees will be co-chaired by senior officials
of each Government.

-- The commission will meet approximately every six months, with the venue alternating
between the two countries.

-- At its meetings, the Commission will review activities of the committees, resolve any
outstanding difficulties and establish an agenda for future undertakings of the Commission. 
Committee co-chairpersons will be responsible for their committees' completing assigned tasks
prior to the next Commission meeting.

-- The inaugural meeting of the Commission will be held in Washington, D.C., on March 1,
1995.

This Statement of Intent may be terminated by either government upon written notice to the
other Government.

DONE at Washington on March 1, 1995, in duplicate.


FOR THE GOVERNMENT OF THE               FOR THE GOVERNMENT OF THE
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA:               REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA:


(signed) Albert Gore, Jr.               (signed)  Thabo Mbeki
</PRE></BODY></HTML>
