<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Working Group on Sustainability and  Agriculture in
the Rural Context</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">
<H2>TERMS OF REFERENCE FOR USA/RSA BINATIONAL   COMMITTEE ON
AGRICULTURE  WORKING GROUP ON SUSTAINABILITY AND  AGRICULTURE IN
THE RURAL CONTEXT</H2>  
<P>NAME 
</P>
<P>	The working group shall be called &#179;The Working Group on
Sustainability and  Agriculture in the Rural Context&#178;.  
</P>
<P>COMPOSITION</P>
<P> 1. 	The Co-Chairpersons will be nominated by the Agriculture
Committee.
</P>
<P>2. 	The Working Group will consist of the Co-Chairpersons and
such other individuals  as each Co-Chairperson may, from time to
time, respectively appoint as members of  the  Working Group,
including representatives from other departments and government 
agencies.  Each Co-Chairperson will keep the other informed as to
the Working Group  membership. 
</P>
<P>3. 	Each Co-Chairperson may appoint a Co-Vice Chairperson to
act in his/her  capacity as Co-Chairperson.
</P>
<P>4.	Each Co-Chairperson will designate a point of contact on
his/her perspective side  for all communications and to organize
administrative staff support for the Working  Group.
</P>
<P> OBJECTIVES  The objective of the Working Group will be to
identify, initiate and support through  mutually agreed
activities in resource utilization, management and conservation,
with  emphasis on the rural sector.  The following areas of
concern will be addressed: 
</P>
<P>*	Sustainable natural agricultural resource utilization
through development of    policy, norms, standards and
guidelines; 
<BR>*	Information, monitoring and audit systems;  
<BR> *	Combating desertification; 
<BR>*	Conservation of biodiversity; 
<BR>*	Reclamation and rehabilitation;  
<BR>*	Promoting a conservation ethic/stewardship: 
<BR>*	Environmental impact assessment 
<BR>*	Technology development - e.g. smallholder irrigation 
</P>
<P>ACTIVITIES  Activities to meet the above objectives will
include the exchange of technical expertise, the  identification
of and participation in collaborative research to enhance
sustainable use of  agricultural natural resources, and the
development of  programs to enhance/develop  capacity of
agricultural scientists and of  rural communities in resource
conservation and  sustainable resource utilization.  Specific
agreed upon activities will be described in Activity
Implementation Plans (AIPs)  that will include a plan of work,
roles and responsibilities, timing, costs and other 
considerations and concurred in by both parties.   These will
include programs to tap the  broad aggregate capacity of  US
agencies in such fields as:  	<BR>- 	natural resource inventory 
<BR>	-	watershed planning and management  	<BR>- 	soil erosion
prediction and prevention  	<BR>-	community conservation
initiatives  	<BR>-	on farm water management   	<BR>-	water
harvesting  	<BR>-	use of GIS in soil and water conservation  
<BR>-	conservation/resource economics  
</P>
<P>MEETINGS OF THE COMMITTEE 
</P>
<P>1.	The Co-Chairpersons will mutually establish the date,
location, time, procedures  and agenda of meetings.  The
Co-Chairperson resident in the country which is the venue  of a
meeting will conduct that meeting. 
</P>
<P>2.	For its meetings, the Working Group may use various
methods of communications  (video or telephone) when practical. 
The Co-Chairpersons will mutually decide who will  conduct any
such meeting. </P>
<P>3. 	All recommendations or decisions of the Working Group
must have the  concurrence of the Co-Chairpersons. 
</P>
<P>4.	The point of contact in the country which is the venue of
a meeting will be  responsible for providing adequate
administrative support for that meeting.  
</P>
<P>RECORD OF PROCEEDINGS/REPORTING  
</P>
<P>1.	The records of each Working Group meeting will be in the
English language, and  distributed to all participants. 
</P>
<P>2.	The Working Group shall report on progress made to the
Committee at its  Biannual meetings.   Concurred in by:
</P>
<P> ________________________________      <BR>
____________________  <BR>Dr. Mishack B. Molope  <BR>Date 
Co-Chairperson, RSA                      </P>
<P>   ________________________________                          
 <BR>_____________________
<BR>Mr. Pearlie S. Reed <BR> Date Co-Chairperson, USA  
</P></BODY></HTML>
