<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Agriculture Committee: Terms of Reference</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">
<H2>AGRICULTURE COMMITTEE OF THE UNITED STATES-SOUTH AFRICA  
BINATIONAL COMMISSION   </H2>
<H2>TERMS OF REFERENCE 
</H2>
<P>On December 5, 1995, the Vice President of the United States
of America and the Executive Deputy President of the Republic of
South Africa, on behalf of their respective countries,
established an Agriculture Committee under the United
States-South Africa Binational Commission for the purpose of
providing a permanent formal venue for high-level discussion of
matters of mutual interest relating to agriculture, including
agriculture as a basis for rural development and agribusiness
development.</P>
<P>On October 31, 1994, the Secretary of Agriculture of the
United States of America and the Minister Without Portfolio of
the Republic of South Africa signed the &quot;Joint Statement of
Shared Principles On Cooperation Between the United States
Department of Agriculture and the South African Office for the
Reconstruction and Development Programme&quot;.</P>
<P>These Terms of Reference are established in furtherance of
cooperation in their mutual interests in agriculture between the
two countries. 
</P>
<P>ARTICLE I
</P>
<P>Purpose 
</P>
<P>1.  A Committee on Agriculture (&quot;the Committee&quot;)
will be established under the United States-South Africa
Binational Commission.
</P>
<P>2.  The purpose of the Committee is to provide a high-level
forum to strengthen bilateral relations between the United States
of America and the Republic of South Africa and to facilitate
discussion and cooperation on agricultural programs, projects,
and exchanges between the two countries in, but not limited to,
the areas of :  natural resource conservation and management;
agricultural technology development for income generation;
institutional development and capacity building; agricultural
trade, investment, and development; marketing, regulation and
safety of food products; food and nutrition; economics,
education, communication, extension and research.</P>
<P>3.  The activities of the Committee are intended to result in
mutual benefits to the United States and to South Africa through
mutual cooperation.
</P>
<P>4.  The Committee may encourage and facilitate the
development of direct contacts and cooperation between private
entities, universities, research centers, institutes, government
agencies, and other entities throughout the United States and
South Africa.</P>
<P>	2  ARTICLE II
</P>
<P>Composition 
</P>
<P>1.  The United States Secretary of Agriculture and the South
African Minister of Agriculture and Land Affairs (hereinafter
referred to as &#179;Co-Chairpersons&#178;) will co-chair the
committee.  
</P>
<P>2.  The committee will consist of the Co-Chairpersons and
such other individuals as each Co-Chairperson, from time to time,
respectively  appoints as members, including representatives from
other ministries and government agencies.  Each Co-Chairperson
will keep the other informed as to the Committee membership.</P>
<P>3.  Each Co-Chairperson may appoint a Co-Vice Chairperson to
act in its capacity as Co-Chairperson.
</P>
<P>4.  Each Co-Chairperson will designate a point of contact on
its respective side for all communications and to organize
administrative staff support for the Committee.</P>
<P>ARTICLE III
</P>
<P>Meetings of the Committee 
</P>
<P>1.  The Co-Chairpersons will establish the date, location,
time, procedure, and agenda of meetings.  The Co-Chairperson
resident in the country which is the venue for a meeting will
conduct that meeting.
</P>
<P>2.  The Committee may conduct meetings through the use of
video-conferencing, tele-conferencing, and other methods of
telecommunication, when practical.  The Co-Chairpersons will
mutually decide who will conduct any such meeting.
</P>
<P>3.  All recommendations or decisions of the Committee will be
subject to the concurrence of the Co-Chairpersons.
</P>
<P>4.  The point of contact in the country which is the venue
for a meeting will be responsible for providing adequate
administrative support for that meeting. 
</P>
<P>ARTICLE IV</P>
<P>Working Groups  	</P>
<P>1.  The Co-Chairpersons may agree to establish working groups
to address particular issues or to facilitate direct contacts in
particular fields of mutual interest.  The working groups may
include representatives from the private sector, non-government
organizations, and community-based organizations.  
</P>
<P>2.  Working groups may meet independently of the Committee.
</P>
<P>3.  Working groups will report to the Committee as the latter
may decide.
</P>
<P>4.  Working groups may be discontinued by either
Co-Chairperson upon written notification to the other
Co-Chairperson.  
</P>
<P>ARTICLE V</P>
<P>					Records
</P>
<P>The records of each Committee meeting and of the meetings of
each working group will be in the English Language. 
</P>
<P>ARTICLE VI
</P>
<P>Limitations  	</P>
<P>1.  The functions and activities of the Committee and any
working group are subject to the availability of funds and
personnel for each country.
</P>
<P>2.  These Terms of Reference are not intended to create
commitments that are binding under international law. 
</P>
<P>ARTICLE VII
</P>
<P>Modification and Termination 
</P>
<P>`	This Declaration may be modified in writing by the two
appropriate authorities in the United States and South Africa,
and may be terminated at any time by either such authority upon
written notice to the other authority.
</P>
<P><BR>For the Department of Agriculture,		
<BR>United States of America;
<BR>__________________________
<BR> Daniel Glickman	
<BR>Secretary of Agriculture 
<BR>__________________________
<BR>Date
</P>
<P><BR>For the National Department of Agriculture,
<BR>Republic of South Africa; 
<BR> ________________________<BR>Derek Andre Hanekom	
<BR>Minister of Agriculture and Land Affairs
<BR>__________________________	
<BR>Date              
</P></BODY></HTML>
