<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Statement at Conclusion</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">
<P>Vice President Al Gore announced today that the Conservation,
Environment and Water Committee of the U.S. - South Africa
Binational Commission, chaired by Secretary of the Interior Bruce
Babbitt, and South African Minister of Water Affairs Kadar Asmal,
 reviewed the progress of its 69 exchange visits sponsored this
year and its 22 projects.  Exchange visits have primarily been
South African officials from the national and provincial levels
of government and non-governmental organizations to the U.S. to
review such subjects as water conservation, waste management,
parks management, pollution abatement, etc. Most exchanges lasted
from two weeks to a month.  Among the 22 projects of the
Committee are included technical assistance on livestock
management in critical resource areas, dam safety, weather
monitoring, and increasing participation of non-governmental
organizations in conservation.  
</P>
<P>The Committee  also had extensive discussions on the
importance of environmental education in both countries.  The
role of non-governmental organizations in Committee activities
was reviewed as well.  The meeting concluded with a discussion of
upcoming multilateral environmental issues of common concern to
both countries. 
</P>
<P>Secretary Babbitt hosted a reception on Monday evening in
honor of the South African delegation at the new offices of the
National Council of Negro Women on Pennsylvania Avenue.    #
</P></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
