</P>
<P>For Immediate Release                                  
December 5, 1995
</P>
<P>U.S.-SOUTH AFRICA BINATIONAL COMMISSION SCIENCE AND
TECHNOLOGY COMMITTEE
</P>
<P>Cooperative Agreement on Agricultural Science and Technology
</P>
<P>At today's meeting of the U.S.-South Africa Binational
Commission, U.S. Vice President Al Gore and South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki announced the completion of a Cooperative
Agreement between the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) and
the South African Agricultural Research Council (ARC) on
Agricultural Science and Technology.  The Cooperative Agreement
was signed on Friday, December 1, by Floyd Horn, Administrator of
