<TITLE></TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">
<H3>United States - South Africa Binational Commission<BR>Human
Resources Development and Education Committee 
</H3>
<PRE>                            Terms of Reference
                                     
I.   The United States - South Africa Human Resources Development
     and Education Committee [the &quot;Committee&quot;] is hereby
     established by the Governments of the Republic of South
     Africa and the United States of America [the &quot;Parties&quot;] as a
     bilateral committee to facilitate cooperation in human
     resource development and education between the Parties. 
     These terms of reference are intended to provide a general
     framework to guide cooperation between the Parties.


II.  The Committee will provide guidance to the Parties, allow
     for information exchange and encourage bilateral discussions
     in mutually agreed upon areas of human resource development
     and education.  These could include:

     1.   Cooperation in specific areas of human resource
          development and the education and training sectors,
          including direct government to government cooperation,
          public/private partnerships, and cooperation between
          non-governmental organizations and private sector firms
          and associations in South Africa and the United States
          of America.

     2.   Policy, regulatory and other barriers to smooth
          implementation of cooperation programmes and solutions
          to such barriers.

     3.   Exchange of information on current South Africa -
          United States of America human resource development and
          education and training activities, especially those
          supported by the governments of South Africa or the
          United States of America.

     4.   Review, agree upon programme priorities, provide policy
          support and visibility to currently planned or ongoing
          initiatives.

III.      The Committee will consist of a South African section
          and a United States of America section.  The Committee
          will be co-chaired by the South African Minister of
          Education and the Administrator for the United States
          Agency for International Development.  The South
          African Minister of Labour and the Director of the
          United States Information Agency will serve as the
          respective deputy co-chairpersons.


IV.       The Committee will consist of senior officials from
          appropriate ministries, government departments and
          entities and relevant representatives from the non-
          governmental sector.  Each chairperson will be
          responsible for ensuring that the views of the human
          resource development, education and training sectors
          are adequately represented within the committee.

V.        The Committee will form, as needed, ad-hoc working
          groups to consider and report on specific matters.  The
          Committee will determine the assignments of such
          working groups which will conduct their work in
          accordance with this agreement.

VI.       The Committee will work on the basis of mutual
          agreement and will, as necessary, adopt rules of
          procedures and works programs.  The Committee will meet
          regularly, as mutually agreed by the Parties
          alternatively in South Africa and the United States of
          America.  Any document agreed upon during the work of
          the Committee will be in the English language.

VII.      These terms of reference may be amended by mutual
          agreement of the Parties at any time.







</PRE></BODY></HTML>
