<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Overview of Research Program</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Overview of Research Program</H1>The Deaconess Hospital has an active research program which is sufficiently broad to support our patient care activities but which emphasizes seven key areas. A relatively high proportion (43%) of principal investigators at the Deaconess are active clinicians and the major areas of our research program directly complement our areas of clinical specialization. The departments of Medicine, Surgery, Radiology, Pathology, Psychiatry, Anesthesia, Nursing and Pharmacy participate in organized research.  <UL>	<LI><A HREF="cardvasc.htm"><B>Cardiovascular Disease</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="infect.htm"><B>Infectious Disease</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="cancer.htm"><B>Cancer/Cell Growth and Differentiation</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="inflame.htm"><B>Inflammation</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="nutrit.htm"><B>Nutrition</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="trnsplnt.htm"><B>Transplantation</B></A>	<LI><A HREF="mindbody.htm"><B>Mind-Body Medicine</B></A></UL><P>The overall growth of the Deaconess program during the past decade has been dramatic for both laboratory and clinical research. <P><B>Total Research Expenses (x 1000) per each fiscal year</B><BLOCKQUOTE>	<B>1990:</B> $16,697<BR>	<B>1991:</B> $19,968<BR>	<B>1992:</B> $20,571<BR>	<B>1993:</B> $25,095<BR>	<B>1994:</B> $28,909<BR>	<B>1995:</B> $27,578</BLOCKQUOTE><P>At present we have over 225 active research projects and 300 active clinical research protocols.  Our research funding is derived from a variety of federal, non-profit and industrial sponsors with the federal share constituting approximately half of the total.  Industrial sponsorship is provided for both laboratory and clinical studies with the latter totaling the larger number. <P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
