<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Referral Information</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Overview</H1><A HREF="about.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="centers.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Referral Information</H2><P><B>How to Refer a Patient</B><BR>Physicians may refer patients for consultation, diagnosis or treatment. If you know the name of the specialist, that physician can be contacted by phone during regular business hours. If a specific physician name is not known, call MediCall, the Deaconess physician referral service, at <B>(800) 472-4800</B>. This referral service is staffed by trained representatives who can assist you in locating the most appropriate specialist. For an emergency admission, the referring physician should call the page operator, <B>(617) 632-8593</B>, and ask for the chief medical or chief surgical officer.<P>The Deaconess physician keeps the referring physician apprised of the patient's treatment and prognosis by phone and through written reports. Frequent contact between physicians is maintained and encouraged. Questions and suggestions also are welcome. A referral bkacground letter, including your patient's symptons, diagnosis, and treatment to date is appreciated.<P><B>How to Transfer a Patient</B><BR>With over 2,300 transfers annually, smooth operations are crucial to providing excellent patient care. Transfers can be arranged by contacting the staff physician in the appropriate department listed in this directory. Psychiatry transfers also may be arranged by calling the Psychiatry Unit at <B>(617) 632-8771</B>. Patient transfers are then coordinated by individuals dedicated to expediting the placement of patients in the appropriate unit. To provide personalized care, each patient's medical history is re-viewed prior to his or her arrival and patient status is reported to the referring physician. <P><B>International Referrals:	632-9889</B><BR>Deaconess staff can assist the international physician in choosing a specialist and can assist international patients with housing, transportation and other special or individual needs.<P>If translation services are required, please refer to <A HREF="../patient/inter.htm">Interpreting Services</A> under the Patient Information section.<P>Communication capabilities for physicians include telex, facsimile and teleconferencing (sending and receiving) via the Hospital satellite network. Follow-up and ongoing communication with the referring physician are priorities for the maintenance of optimal continuing care.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
