<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Admitting and Registration</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Patient Information</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="inter.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Admitting and Registration</H2><P>Director: Noreen Hurley <B>754-2219</B><P>The admitting physician on the Deaconess staff will contact the Admitting Department to arrange a bed assignment and clarify the insurance requirements for all admissions. Elective admissions will receive a pre-admission packet if time allows, and patients may be called at home to obtain demographic and insurance information prior to the day of admission. All patients are asked to bring copies of their insurance cards with them at the time of admission, or to have a family member bring it in for them if they are admitted urgently. <P>Patients coming through the admission area receive their initial testing in the pre-admission testing area and are escorted to their rooms by the admitting staff. Urgent and emergent patients, including transfers from other facilities, are screened by nursing coordinators to ensure placement in the proper unit and efficient utilization of ancillary services. Communication with transferring hospitals assists in clarifying clinical details. Precertification approval is also required on managed-care patients prior to their admission, unless clinically impossible. Financial counselors are available to assist patients if necessary. Personnel are available 24 hours a day to coordinate admissions.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
