<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Accommodations</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Patient Information</H1><A HREF="inter.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="direct.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Accommodations</H2><P><B>Local Accommodations</B><P>The Deaconess Hospital Visitor's Guide contains the names of hotels, motels and guest houses in the area. Many of these accommodations offer lower rates to Hospital patients and their relatives. The guide also lists restaurants, shopping areas and other useful local services. It is available by contacting the Admitting Office, <B>754-2219</B>. Special needs arrangements for patients and their families may be coordinated by calling the Department of Social Work, <B>632-7250</B>.<P><B>Guest Accommodations</B><P><B>Director: Jean Proestakis<BR>Reservations: 632-8128</B><P>Guest accommodations are available for patients and their families who must stay near the Hospital before or after their hospital stay. Special discounted room rates are offered at the Best Western Boston -- The Inn at Children's, located two blocks from the Hospital. There are a limited number of rooms and reservations are required. For more information, please call the Reservation Office at <B>632-8128</B>. <P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
