<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directions to Deaconess Hospital</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Patient Information</H1><A HREF="accommod.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="maps.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Directions to Deaconess Hospital</H2><P><H3>By Car:</H3><B>From the North:</B><BR>Heading south on I-93 or Route 1, take Storrow Drive westbound. Take the Fenway-Route 1 South exit and then the first right onto Boylston Street. Follow Boylston Street to the third set of lights (intersection of Park Drive, Boylston Street and Brookline Avenue). Bear left onto Brookline Avenue, follow through two sets of lights to a third set at Longwood Avenue. Turn right onto Longwood and left at the first street (Pilgrim Road).<P><B>From the West:</B><BR>Heading east on the Massachusetts Turnpike, take Route 128 south to Route 9 east. Take Route 9 through Brookline Village to the intersection with Brookline Avenue (the Brook House will be on your right). Bear left onto Brookline Avenue and follow through three sets of lights (past the Deaconess Hospital sign on your left) to the fourth set at Longwood Avenue. Turn left, and left again at the first street (Pilgrim Road).<P><B>From the South:</B><BR>Heading north on I-93 (Southeast Expressway), take the Massachusetts Avenue-Roxbury exit. At the end of the ramp, cross Massachusetts Avenue onto Melnea Cass Boulevard. Follow Cass Blvd. to Tremont Street and take a left, then your first right onto Ruggles Street. At the intersection of Ruggles and Huntington Avenue, turn left onto Huntington Avenue and follow it to Longwood Avenue. Turn right, and go through two sets of traffic lights (past Brookline Avenue). One block past Brookline Avenue, turn left onto Pilgrim Road.<P><B>From the Southwest:</B><BR>From Route 128, head north on Route 1. Follow Route 1 into Boston, past Route 9 exit and Brookline Avenue traffic lights to Longwood Avenue. Turn right onto Longwood Avenue and then right onto Pilgrim Road.<P><H3>Parking:</H3>Parking is available in the Deaconess Hospital garage located at the corner of Pilgrim Road and Longwood Avenue, one block from the Hospital's main entrance. Additional parking is available in the garage next to the Lowry Medical Office Building, 110 Francis Street (at the corner of Francis Street and Brookline Avenue). <A HREF="maps.htm">(See the maps)</A><P><H3>By Public Transportation:</H3><P>MBTA bus #66 (Harvard Square to Dudley Station via Allston and Brookline Village), MBTA bus #39 and the Arborway/Copley Square bus (replacing the Arborway-Huntington Avenue trolley) all stop at Brigham Circle near Francis Street. Walk north on Francis Street to Brookline Avenue. Cross Brookline Avenue and continue up Francis Street one block. Turn right; the main Hospital entrance is on your left.<P>MBTA bus #47 (Albany Street to Central Square, Cambridge, via the Longwood Medical Area), which also services the Ruggles Street Orange Line/Commuter Rail Station, stops at the corner of Brookline Avenue and Longwood Avenue. Walk west on Brookline Avenue one block past Longwood. Turn right at Joslin Park/Deaconess Road, walk up one block, turn left, and the Hospital entrance is on your right.<P>MBTA Bus #65 (Brighton Center to Kenmore Square via Washington Street and Brookline Avenue) and MBTA Bus #60 (Chestnut Hill to Kenmore Station via Cypress Street and Brookline Avenue) stop at the corner of Brookline Avenue and Deaconess Road. Head north on Deaconess Road one block, turn left, and the Hospital entrance is on your right.<P>Riverside trolley (Green line "D") stops at Longwood station. Walk west on Chapel Street (up a hill) to Longwood Avenue. Turn left onto Longwood, crossing the bridge over the trolley tracks. Cross Route 1 (the Riverway) and walk two blocks (past Autumn Street on your right) to Pilgrim Road. Turn right and walk up one block. The Hospital entrance is on your right.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
