<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Directory Services</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="clinical/index.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Introduction</H2>We are pleased to provide you with the Deaconess Hospital Physician Directory. This directory describes our areas of medical expertise, major clinical departments, our medical staff and specialized Hospital services.<P>Developing and maintaining strong relationships with referring physicians in the community is very important to us. As a tertiary care referral center for community doctors and hospitals, we care for patients with complicated medical and surgical problems and then work with primary care physicians who provide for their patients' ongoing health-care needs. Our doctors are easily accessible for consultation by telephone, and they provide timely reports on patient status on a regular basis. Deaconess Hospital also offers MediCall, our physician referral service, to assist you in selecting a specialist for your patients.<P>Deaconess Hospital is a part of an emerging health-care network, which also includes Deaconess-Glover Hospital in Needham, MA; Deaconess-Nashoba Hospital in Ayer, MA; and the New England Baptist Hospital in Boston. The goal of the network is to have community hospitals and physicians serve as the core of comprehensive health and medical services within the geographic areas they serve, while providing patients with seamless access to highly trained specialists and subspecialists at tertiary centers when needed. The network also facilitates patient access to other affiliated institutions, including Children's Hospital, Beth Israel Hospital, the Joslin Diabetes Center, the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and the Joint Center for Radiation Therapy. <P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
