<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Inflammation</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Overview of Research Program</H1><A HREF="cancer.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="nutrit.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Inflammation</H2><P>In conjunction with the New England Baptist Hospital, another hospital within the Pathway Health Network, we will locate a group of newly recruited investigators who study inflammation within our new laboratory space.  This group includes Dr. Steven Goldring, Dr. Philip Auron, Dr. Debra Galson and Dr. Mary Goldring.  They are interested in those inflammatory events which occur in the setting of artificial implants into bone (such as artificial hips and knees) and have been dissecting the inflammatory events using the tools of cell and molecular biology.  The group has cloned two forms of the calcitonin receptor which regulates the uptake of calcium in bones and a cytokine designated Il-1b, one of the soluble protein mediators of inflammatory reactions.  All of the members of this group participate in an NIH funded program project grant.  In addition, Drs. Auron and S. Goldring both also have RO1 grants from NIH while Dr. M. Goldring has independent support from the Arthritis Foundation.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
