<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Mind-Body Medicine</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Overview of Research Program</H1><A HREF="trnsplnt.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="index.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Mind-Body Medicine</H2><P>Dr. Herbert Benson has pioneered the careful study of how the mind influences disease and his work continues within the Mind-Body Medical Institute.  While a great deal of anecdotal information on the mind-body connection exists, few investigators have skillfully applied rigorous methods of medical research to this topic.  Dr. Benson and his staff are engaged in such research and have demonstrated how techniques such as the Relaxation Response can be successfully applied in circumstances ranging from stress reduction through pain management and smoking cessation to infertility.  The groups work is supported by a combination of federal, private non-profit, company and philanthropic organizations.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
