ogy Conference</I><P>Noon<BR>Meissner 118<BR><I>Tumor Conference</I><P><B>Mon., April 1 at Noon</B><BR>Kennedy G7<BR><I>Cardiovascular Grand Round</I><BR>"Medical Management of the Coronary Patient: Is It a Lost Art?"<BR>Thomas J. Ryan, M.D.<BR>Boston University School of Medicine<P><B>Wed., April 3 at 7am</B><BR>CC2-C<BR><B>Cardiothoracic Surgery Teaching Rounds</B><BR>"Intraoperative Myocardial Management Strategies State of the Art 1996"<BR>Irvin Krukenkamp, M.D.<P>7:15am<BR>Meissner 118<BR><I>Surgical Oncology Rounds</I><P>8am<BR>Joslin Auditorium<BR><I>Surgical Grand Rounds</I><BR>"Research and Clinical Practice: A Practical Approach"<BR>Richard Pearl, M.D.<BR>Hospital for Sick Children<P>12:30pm<BR>Joslin Auditorium<BR><I>Division of General Internal Medicine Clinical Conference</I><BR>"Management of Common Hand Problems"<BR>Nancy Falco-Chedid, M.D.<P><B>Thu., April 4 at 11am</B><BR>CC782<BR><I>Neurology Conference</I><P>Noon<BR>Meissner 118<I>Tumor Conference</I><P><HR><P><H3>Hospital Events</H3><B>Alpha Credit Union announces spring specials</B><BR>Alpha Credit Union rates are going up and down! On March 1, the Credit Union raised the rate on its share accounts to 3.03 percent APY and on its vacation and Christmas Clubs to 2.77 percent APY. Alpha also is offering a spring loan special; loans of $1,000 to $2,500 are being offered at a reduced APR of 9.9 percent. Move fast, as this special expires on <B>Fri., March 29.</B> For details on these and other offers, call the Credit Union at <B>2-0446.</B><P><B>Nursing scholarship offered</B><BR>Deaconess employees enrolled in a registered nurse program and within one year of graduation may qualify for a Department of Nursing scholarship to help defray tuition costs. For application information, call <B>Donna Quinn,</B> Department of Nursing, at <B>2-0958.</B> Completed applications must be submitted by <B>Fri., March 29.</B><P><B>Gift Shop to hold plant sale and raffle drawing</B><BR>Just in time for spring planting, the Gift Shop will hold a plant sale on <B>Thu., April 4</B> from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. in the Farr lobby. Items for sale will include potted bulbs and custom-made baskets full of various spring bulbs. On <B>Fri., April 5</B>, the Gift Shop will hold its spring raffle drawing for the prize of a large, white, stuffed Easter bunny, valued at $150. Raffle chances are on sale until the moment of the drawing and costs 50 cents each or three for $1.<P><B>Hospital announces second summer celebration</B><BR>Mark your calendar! In appreciation of the hard work by staff and employees throughout the year, the Hospital will host its second summer celebration on <B>Sat., Jul 27</B> at Glen Ellen Country Club in Millis.<P><B>"Heart and Sole" program targets lifestyle changes to reverse heart disease.</B><BR>The Division of Behavioral Medicine is offering a 20-week program, "Heart and Sole," that focuses on exercise, nutrition, relaxation techniques, and stress management to reduce the symptons of coronary artery disease. For more information, call <B>2-7378.</B><P><B>BC/BS representative available to answer insurance questions</B><BR>A Blue Cross and Blue Shield (BC/BS) representative will be available the second and fourth Friday of each month to answer any questions regarding the BC/BS Master Health, Blue Care Elect, Heatlhflex Blue, and Network Blue medical plans. The BC/BS representative will be in the Benefits Office, located on the first floor of 21 Autumn Street, from 9 to 11 a.m. Please bring your health plan identification card and any bills. For more information, call <B>Katherine Heavey</B> at <B>2-8223.</B><P><B>Training opportunities fliers available</B><BR>Spring 1996 training opportunities fliers are available. To obtain a copy, call <B>2-7188</B> or stop by the Benefits Office, located on the first floor of 21 Autumn Street, and pick one up from the literature rack.<P><B>News and notes</B><BR>The next issue of <I>Calendar</I> will be published on <B>Mon., April 8.</B> The deadline for submitting material is noon on <B>Wed., April 3</B>. Please send <I>Calendar</I> submissions to <B>Marquita Dunbar</B>, Office of Communications, MASCO4, or fax them to <B>2-7150</B>.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
