<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Centers of Excellence</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Centers of Excellence</H1><A HREF="centers.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="diabetes.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>AIDS/HIV</H2><P>Deaconess Hospital has earned a reputation for combining state-of-the-art medical technology with an unmatched spirit of caring in its treatment of patients with AIDS. Treatment focuses on providing cost-effective care to minimize hospitalization and deliver greater comfort and quality of life to each patient.<P>In addition to using standard forms of treatment for HIV itself as well as complicating opportunistic infections and malignancies, physicians in the Division of Infectious Disease participate in clinical trials of new treatments and innovative combinations of licensed agents. The trials, which are conducted in collaboration with the National Institutes of Health and various international pharmaceutical companies, provide patients access to 'cutting-edge' therapy that would otherwise not be available. Recent areas of particular interest include new antiretroviral compounds (non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitors and protease inhibitors) as well as immune-based therapies of HIV and HIV-related malignancies. Many patients who are interested in innovative therapies have the opportunity to participate in these clinical trials of new treatment modalities.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
