<H1>Special Clinical Programs</H1>
<A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="dph.htm">[NEXT]</A>
<H2>Boston Center for Liver Cancer/Rebecca Murray Hepatobiliary Research Unit</H2>

<B>Director:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Keith Stuart, M.D.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Staff:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        <A HREF="#staff">See Below</A>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Appointments:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Call 617-632-8645<BR>
        Fax: 617-566-8043
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Location:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Deaconess Hospital<BR>
        110 Francis Street<BR>
        Boston, Massachusetts 02215<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Email Inquiries:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        <A HREF="mailto:kstuart@nedhmail.nedh.harvard.edu">Boston Center For Liver Cancer</A>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>             
The Boston Center for Liver Cancer is a new program established at Deaconess Hospital to help study and care for patients with cancers of the liver, bile ducts or pancreas.  Designed to address all aspects of care of these diseases with their complicated medical problems, the Center is staffed by specialists in the fields of Medical Oncology, Hepatobiliary Surgery, Gastroenterology, Interventional Radiology, and Radiation Oncology.  Allied members of the Department of Nursing, Social Work, and Nutrition, who specialize in cancer care, are involved as well.
<P>
This multidisciplinary, disease-specific approach concentrates the expertise of multiple physicians so that each patient receives the most complete evaluation and recommendations possible.  Consultations and testing are all coordinated by the Center so that decisions regarding diagnosis and therapy can be made quickly and efficiently, with a minimum number of visits.  In addition, patients may be included in appropriate ongoing research studies investigating new treatment options.
<P>
The Center is dedicated to providing an organized focus on individuals with all forms of cancer involving the hepatobiliary system, while integrating exceptional patient care with quality research.
<P>
<B>Specializing in:</B>
<P>
<UL>
        <LI>Hepatocellular carcinoma
        <LI>Cholangiocarcinoma
        <LI>Gallbladder carcinoma
        <LI>Neuroendocrine metastases (Islet cell, carcinoid)
        <LI>Colorectal metastases
        <LI>Liver metastases
</UL>
<P>
<B>Current research/treatment programs include:</B>
<P>
<UL>
        <LI>Surgical resection
        <LI>Cryosurgery
        <LI>Chemoembolization
        <LI>Systemic chemotherapy
        <LI>Intra-arterial chemotherapy
        <LI>Radiation therapy
        <LI>Combined modality treatments
        <LI>Investigational agents
        <LI>Percutaneous delivery of chemotherapy
</UL>
<A NAME="staff"></A>
<P>
