<H2>Deaconess PRO Health</H2>
<P>
<B>Program Director:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Jayne Carvelli-Sheehan,M.S.N., R.N., C.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Program Manager:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Wanda Shelton, M.S.W., M.B.A.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Corporate Sales:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Patricia Saint Aubin
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<B>Inquiries:</B>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
        Call 632-8050
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
Deaconess PRO Health offers wellness and health promotion programs to the corporate community within the metropolitan Boston area.
<P>
PRO Health organizes hospital staff, including physicians, nurses, psychologists, nutritionists and physical therapists, in implementing health risk management programs at the workplace. The goal is to enable employers and their respective employees to make informed decisions concerning health issues while promoting the good will of Deaconess Hospital in the corporate community.
<P>
<B>Programs:</B>
<P>
<UL>
        <LI>Health Risk Appraisal
        <LI>Nutritional Management
        <LI>Smoking Cessation
        <LI>Stress Management
        <LI>CPR Training
</UL>
<P>
<B>Screenings:</B>
<P>
<UL>
        <LI>Blood Pressure Screening
        <LI>Body Composition Screening
        <LI>Low-fat Cooking Demonstrations
        <LI>Cholesterol Screening
        <LI>Glucose Screening
        <LI>Podiatry Clinic
        <LI>Breast Care Clinic
</UL>
<P>
<B>Seminars:</B>
<P>
<UL>
        <LI>Back Injury Prevention
        <LI>Elder Care
        <LI>Ergonomics
        <LI>Exercise
        <LI>Information About and Prevention of Infectious<BR>Diseases including AIDS
        <LI>Nutrition
        <LI>Psychology
        <LI>Skin Cancer
        <LI>Stress Management
        <LI>Women's Health Issues
</UL>
<P>

