<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Special Clinical Programs</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="etc.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Diabetes Treatment Unit</H2><B>Medical Director:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Richard S. Beaser, M.D.<BR>	Phone: 632-8798</BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Diabetes Treatment Unit (DTU) provides comprehensive diabetes treatment and patient education for patients requiring inpatient care for their diabetes control and/or other medical conditions. Diabetes management issues addressed include newly diagnosed diabetes, initiation of insulin therapy, initiation of intensive diabetes therapy management programs and assessment of diabetes control problems when outpatient efforts have failed or are otherwise inappropriate. The format begins the process of optimizing metabolic control and encourages patients and significant others to participate as active members of the healthcare team. Opportunities to learn and to be motivated are made available to every patient according to his/her individuals needs and abilities to comprehend.<P>The DTU is a joint Joslin Diabetes Center/Deaconess effort combining the expertise and experience of these two institutions in this efficient cost-effective intervention. The DTU program is a team approach that involves the patient, physician, diabetes nurse educators, and nutritionists in a concentrated and coordinated effort to develop an individual program of total diabetes care that the patient can manage at home. The patient's glucose management program is assessed, and improvements in the self-treatment program are designed and initiated. The DTU provides a controlled setting for this team of multi-disciplinary specialists to closely monitor blood sugar levels and insulin doses, diet and exercise patterns. In addition, the patient is instructed on the essentials of self-care techniques including insulin use, meal planning , exercise and complications avoidance. Following the DTU inpatient stay further outpatient follow-up with either a member of the Joslin team or the primary care giver can utilize the changes initiated in the DTU to achieve optimal glucose control.<P>Deaconess Hospital and the Joslin Diabetes Center are committed to caring for the special needs of people with diabetes. If needed, subspecialty consultations can be arranged with Joslin ophthalmologists, renal specialists, podiatrists, exercise physiologists and mental health professionals.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
