<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Special Clinical Programs</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="ipc.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Enterostomal Therapy Clinic</H2><B>Medical Directors:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Ronald Bleday, M.D.<BR>	<I>Colorectal Surgery</I>	<P>	Albert Bothe, Jr., M.D.<BR>	<I>General Surgery</I>	<P>	Robert Eyre, M.D.<BR>	<I>Urology</I></BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Referrals:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Call 632-9780</BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Enterostomal Therapy Clinic provides multimodality consultation for the acute and rehabilitative care of individuals with select disorders of the gastrointestinal, genitourinary, and integumentary systems. The Clinic is staffed by two enterostomal therapy nurses, Donna Quinn, R.N., E.T., and Paula Hayes, R.N., E.T., who can be reached at 632-8420.<P>For the patient who has or may need the creation of an ostomy, the following are available:<UL>	<LI>pre-operative teaching and stoma site selections	<LI>postoperative assessment of the stoma and peristomal skin and evaluation of the effectiveness of the pouching system used	<LI>postoperative counseling in adjusting to living with an ostomy, including dietary, sexual and vocational issues	<LI>the evaluation and treatment of stoma and peristomal skin complications	<LI>obtaining sterile catheterized samples from urostomy patients</UL><P>In addition, the Clinic can provide assistance in assessing and recommending ways to manage fistula/wound care, dermal ulcer care, and skin breakdown associated with urinary and/or fecal incontinence.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
