<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Special Clinical Programs</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="sevobese.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Rehabilitation Services</H2><B>Program Director:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Cathy Ball, M.S., P.T.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Appointments:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Call 632-8443</BLOCKQUOTE><P>Rehabilitation Services provides a complete range of physical, occupational, and speech therapies on both an inpatient and outpatient basis. All services require a prescription for consultation from the referring physician. Ongoing dialogue between the therapist and the physician during the patient's rehabilitation program is encouraged.<P>Physical therapy offers functional mobility evaluation and training; evaluation and treatment of musculoskeletal dysfunction (stiffness, weakness, pain and muscle spasm); pre-operative conditioning to enhance recovery; orthotic/prosthetic evaluation and training; and discharge planning, including use of walkers, crutches, canes and other assistive devices. Modalities and equipment available include Kincom isokinetic equipment, BTE Work Simulator, as well as the more common rehab modalities. Outpatient cardiac rehabilitation services are coordinated through the Division of Behavioral Medicine.<P>The PT outpatient program also offers pool therapy programs for treatment of athletic injuries, back pain, arthritis, general conditioning, etc., as well as the use of complete free weights, CYBEX (similar to Nautilus), weight rooms and indoor track for more progressive rehabilitation.<P>Occupational therapy offers upper extremity evaluation, strengthening and range of motion; splinting; training  in self-feeding, dysphagia and activities of daily living (ADL); adaptive equipment for ADL; and perceptual evaluation and treatment.  Modalities available are paraffin and whirlpool as well as the Baltimore Therapeutic Equipment (BTE) Work Simulator for upper extremity rehabilitation.<P>Occupational therapy now offers rehabilitative programs designed around the BTE. This unit can simulate most sports and vocational activities and is used for both assessment and treatment of those functional activities.<P>Speech therapy offers evaluation and treatment of swallowing and speech disorders as well as impaired hearing, perception, and cognition due to illness, disease or trauma. Treatments include instruction in the use of communication boards, electrolarynx and prostheses; swallowing programs, with guidance as to diet, based on patient's ability to swallow to avoid aspiration; follow-up for hearing aid if indicated; activities to assist patients in improving their level of perception or cognition; and assistance in discharge planning.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
