<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Special Clinical Programs</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="travel.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Transitional Care Unit</H2><B>Medical Director:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Richard L. Goldstein, M.D.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Appointments:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Call 232-7717</BLOCKQUOTE><P>This 23-bed unit is for the patient with special medical needs that are not severe enough to require a hospital stay yet are too complex to be met at a traditional nursing home. The Unit provides skilled nursing, rehabilitative and other related clinical services to help the patient regain and maximize functional abilities. All services are overseen by the Unit's Medical Director.<P>The Unit offers a lower cost alternative to using acute inpatient beds for sub-acute patients. Some advantages include early intervention, coordination of post-hospital care, shorter length of stay, increased attention to functional ability and more direct nursing care. The TCU is licensed as a skilled nursing facility and, therefore, requires an interagency referral and a completed hospital medical discharge summary at the time of discharge to the TCU.<P>Skilled and restorative nursing care is provided 24 hours a day. Physical, occupational and speech therapists develop individualized plans to maximize the patient's potential and facilitate independent living. Social workers offer comprehensive discharge planning and arrangements for continued services at home.<P>Patients are referred to the Transitional Care Unit by their admitting physician and discharge planners.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
