<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Nursing</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="index.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Enterostomal Therapy Nurses</H2><B>Director</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Paula Hayes, RN, CETN 	<P>				Donna Quinn, BSN, RN, CETN </BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Beeper</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	2474</BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Office Number</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	(617) 632-8420</BLOCKQUOTE><P>Enterostomal Therapy (ET) Nurses specialize in the care of patients with selected disorders of the gastrointestinal, genitourinary, and integumentary systems. The ET nurses are available to consult with health care team members for the nursing management of patients having needs in the following areas:<P><UL>	<LI><B>Stoma Care</B>	<P>	<UL>		<LI>Pre and post operative education and counseling 		<LI>Select and mark stoma sites 		<LI>Plan post-discharge care and follow-up in the Enterostomal Therapy Clinic 		<LI>Community Resources 	</UL>	<P>	<LI><B>Draining Wounds, Fistulas and Percutaneous Tubes</B>	<P>	<UL>		<LI>Contain drainage and control order 		<LI>Prevent and treat skin breakdown 		<LI>Wound management 	</UL>	<P>	<LI><B>Pressure Ulcers and Incontinence</B>	<P>	<UL>		<LI>Identify patients at risk 		<LI>Initiate prevention and treatment<b> </b>measures 		<LI>Screen patients for needs for therapeutic mattresses/beds 		<LI>Assist staff in teaching patients intermittent self catheterization	</UL>	<P>	<LI><B>Education	<P>	<UL>		<LI>For patient and staff in the aforementioned areas 	</UL></UL><P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
