to further enhance the Deaconess. My goal is to ensure that each member of the Deaconess family be engaged in this pursuit both individually and as part of the team."<P>J. Richard Gaintner, M.D., president and CEO of Pathway Health Network, says the leadership changes are of great significance to the Network's continuing development. "Albert Washko and Robert Norton possess the experience and management talent necessary to help guide our organization well into the next century."<P>Pathway Health Network, established in 1994, is a system of physicians, and community and teaching hospitals, providing comprehensive health care services. Hospitals in the network include Deaconess Hospital and New England Baptist Hospital in Boston, Deaconess-Nashoba Hospital in 	Ayer, Deaconess-Glover Hospital in Needham, and Deaconess-Waltham 	Hospital in Waltham.<P>Deaconess Hospital is a 385-bed tertiary care facility and a major teaching hospital of Harvard Medical School. Established in 1896, the Hospital is internationally recognized for medical expertise in organ transplantation, diabetes, cardiovascular disease, cancer, and AIDS.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
