be of great significance to the Network's continuing development. "Albert Washko will spearhead integration throughout the Network. His management and health care administration experience invaluable assets to the organization."<P>Washko has received two Master's degrees, one in Health Care Administration from the University of Washington and the other in Social Welfare from the University of California Los Angeles. He received a Bachelor's degree in Psychology from California State University. In 1987, Washko received the Meritorious Executive Rank Award from President Reagan when he worked in the Veterans Administration Health System.<P>Pathway Health Network, established in 1994, is a system of physicians, and community and teaching hospitals, providing comprehensive health care services. Hospitals in the network include Deaconess Hospital and New England Baptist Hospital in Boston, Deaconess-Nashoba Hospital in Ayer, Deaconess-Glover Hospital in Needham, and Deaconess-Waltham Hospital in Waltham.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
