: 632-9004	<P>	Ronald G. Bardawil, M.D.<BR>	<I>Director, Cytopathology Laboratory; general anatomic/surgical pathology, exfoliative and fine needle aspiration</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9007	<P>	Ann W. Crosson, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology, renal disease</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9005	<P>	Umberto DeGirolami, M.D. (consultant)<BR>	<I>neuropathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9015	<P>	Micheline Federman, Ph.D.<BR>	<I>Director, Electron Microscopy; metabolic bone pathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-0200	<P>	Jihad Hayek, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-1167	<P>	Urmila Khettry, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology, liver disease, gastrointestinal disease</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9009	<P>	Merle A. Legg, M.D.<BR>	<I>pulmonary disease, neoplasms, endocrine pathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9102	<P>	Massimo Loda, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology, immunopathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-0997	<P>	William C. Quist, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology, cardiovascular pathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-0933	<P>	Steven Tahan, M.D.<BR>	<I>general anatomic/surgical pathology, breast pathology, dermatopathology</I><BR>	Phone: 632-9020</BLOCKQUOTE><P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
