<HTML><HEAD>	<TITLE>Directory Services</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><H1>Welcome to Deaconess Hospital Online</H1><A HREF="../../../overview/index.htm">OVIERVIEW</A>|<A HREF="../../../patient/index.htm">PATIENT INFORMATION</A>|<A HREF="../../../direct/index.htm">DIRECTORY</A>|<A HREF="../../../research/index.htm">RESEARCH</A><BR><A HREF="../../../educate/index.htm">EDUCATION</A>|<A HREF="../../../news/index.htm">NEWS &amp; CONFERENCES</A>|<A HREF="../../../employ/index.htm">EMPLOYMENT</A>|<A HREF="../../../new/index.htm">WHAT'S NEW</A></CENTER><H1>Behavioral Medicine Programs</H1><A HREF="index.htm">[BACK]</A> <A HREF="general.htm">[NEXT]</A><H2>Cardiac Rehabilitation</H2><B>Program Director:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	 Eileen Stuart, M.S., R.N., C.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Medical Directors:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Regis A. de Silva, M.D.<BR>	William Siegel, M.D., M.P.H.</BLOCKQUOTE><P><B>Appointments:</B><P><BLOCKQUOTE>	Call 632-9527</BLOCKQUOTE><P>Offered in collaboration with the Division of Cardiology, this program is designed to condition patients aerobically and modify cardiac risk factors.<P>The Cardiac Rehabilitation Program differs from other programs which focus solely on exercise. This DPA certified program integrates medical and behavioral treatments of cardiovascular disease and includes supervised monitored exercise, relaxation response training, stress management, individualized nutrition counseling and consultations on risk factor reduction. <P>A multidisciplinary team consisting of a cardiologist, cardiac nurse specialist, physical therapist, registered dietitian and relaxation therapist staff the program.<P>Appropriate patients include those with newly diagnosed coronary artery disease, post-MI, post-PTCA, and post-CABG, as well as identified high-risk patients.<P><H5>Copyright 1996 Deaconess Hospital, All rights reserved.</H5></BODY></HTML>
