<BODY BACKGROUND="marble.jpg"><center>
<img src="line.gif">
<center><font size=4><b>The Eighth Annual Corporate Contingency 
Planning Seminar and Exhibition<br></b></font>
<br><font size=4><b>
March 9-12, 1997<br>
San Diego, CA</center><br></font></b>
<br>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>REGISTRATION INFORMATION
<br>
$695.00 IF YOU REGISTER BY JANUARY 9, 1997 <br></B></FONT>
<img src="line.gif"></center>
<br>

Register by FAX: <br>
For immediate registration please FAX page 16 to (314) 894-7474, 24 hours a day.<br>
<br>
Register by mail:  <br>
Send the Conference Registration Form on page 16 to:<br>
	Conference Registrar<br>
	The Disaster Recovery Journal<br>
	P.O. Box 510110<br>
	St. Louis, MO  63151<br>
<br>
Registration Information and Questions:<br>
Call (314) 894-0276 for additional information and/or questions.  Office hours are 9:00 a.m.-5:00 p.m. Central Standard Time, Monday - Friday.<br>
<br>
Conference Hotel:  <br>
	Sheraton San Diego Hotel & Marina<br>
	1380 Harbor Island Drive<br>
	San Diego, CA 92101-1092<br>
	(619) 692-2265<br>
<br>
Hotel Accommodations:  <br>
	To reserve a room, please contact the Sheraton San Diego Hotel & Marina directly at (619) 692-2265.  The group rate is $142 plus tax for a single or a double room per night.  The conference hotel will hold a limited number of rooms at the conference rate until 30 days prior to conference dates. <br>
  Be sure to make your reservations as early as possible.  Mention that you are a Disaster Recovery Conference attendee to receive the  conference rate for your hotel room.  A special government rate is available.  Inquire with the hotel when making your reservation.<br>
<br>
Registration Fee & Registration Hours: <br>
	The fee must be paid prior to this event.   Please send your payment with your registration, or we will bill your company. 
Registration will be available from 1:00 - 8:00 p.m. on Sunday, March 9 and from 7:30-8:30 a.m. on Monday, March 10. <br><br>
Seminar Hours:  <br>
	The seminar hours will be from 2:00 - 5:00 p.m. on Sunday, March 9; 8:00 a.m. to 5:15 p.m. on Monday, March 10; 8:00 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. on Tuesday, March 11; and from 8:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. on Wednesday, March 12. <br>
<br>
Conference Fee: <br>
	Conference fee is $895.00 per person.  Early registration discounts are available as follows:  <br> 		Through January 9-----$695.00 per person<br>
	Jan. 10- Feb. 12-------$795.00  per person<br>
	Feb. 13- March 9------$895.00 per person<br>
	Fee includes all conference materials, notebook, continental breakfasts, luncheons and participation in the workshop forums and breakout sessions. Fee also includes a welcome reception on Sunday evening and a hospitality on Tuesday. Hotel accommodations, airfare, car rental, CDRP exam and DRI courses are not included.  	<br>	
<br>
Disaster Recovery Institute CDRP Exam Fee:<br>
	The CDRP Examination fee is $200.00.  This includes fees for processing the Application for Certification through the DRI International, 1810 Craig Rd. Suite 125, St. Louis, MO  63146, (314) 434-2272.<br>
<br>
Disaster Recovery Institute Course Fee:<br>
	The Disaster Recovery Institute course fee for seminar participants is $525.  This fee includes the CDRP Examination for those taking any of the six sessions. The fee for non-seminar attendees is $595 per course.<br>
<br>
Airfare Discounts:<br>
	Group rates for airfare will be offered. Detailed information will be provided with registration. Certain restrictions will apply.<br>
<br>
Cancellation Policy (MUST BE IN WRITING):<br>
	Cancellations made 30 days prior to the first day of the seminar will be refunded in full.  Cancellations after that date are subject to a 23% service charge.  All "no shows" will be charged the full amount. <br>










