<HEAD><TITLE>type_Document_Title_here</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="marble.jpg"><center>
<img src="line.gif">
<center><font size=4><b>The Eighth Annual Corporate Contingency 
Planning Seminar and Exhibition<br></b></font>
<br><font size=4><b>
March 9-12, 1997<br>
San Diego, CA</center><br></font></b>
<br>
<img src="line.gif"></center>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR><TD bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width=350>
Whats New?<br>
<br>
7 General Sessions<br>
24 Breakout Sessions<br>
3 Issues and Answers Sessions<br>
5 Sunday Workshops<br>
Prize Drawings in Exhibit Hall<br>
Expanded Exhibit Hours<br>
Lunch Areas Located Upstairs<br>
<br><center>
<IMG SRC="photos/sheraton.gif"><br><font size=2><EM>San Diegos Sheraton Hotel and Marina will be the site of the best conference for learning the DR industry.</EM></font>
<br>
<IMG SRC="photos/jamesw1.gif"><EM><font size=2><br>FEMA Director James Witt will discuss public and private sectors DR issues.</EM>

<IMG SRC="photos/davidn1.gif"><EM><font size=2><br>David Nolan, Comdisco  president, will speak on the industry standards. </EM>

<IMG SRC="photos/michae~1.gif"><EM><font size=2><br>Sungard President, Michael Mulholland, will discuss DRs new era. </EM>



</TD><TD>
<STRONG>Why Attend This Conference?</STRONG><br>
As the industrys meeting place, this conference is the place for anyone interested in learning the latest in contingency planning. Youll gain insight into recent trends, meet industry leaders, and learn leadership and team-building skills. The networking and learning possibilities are endless. And you can even customize your schedule to fit your needs. With 31 sessions and 11 workshops,  youll come away with a years worth of ideas in just a few days.<br>
Weve made numerous updates and improvements to this years conference agenda, including additional sessions, new topics and a greater assortment of speakers from which to choose. So now there are even more reasons to attend. Dont miss out on this opportunity to be a part of the largest gathering of contingency planners in the world. The benefits are endless.<br>
<br>
<STRONG>Who Should Attend?</STRONG><br>
Anyone interested in disaster recovery planning should plan to attend this conference. We have information for everyone - from beginners to experts. <br>
Our conference attracts individuals from a variety of industries, providing ideal networking and problem-solving opportunities for our attendees. Industries represented in the past have included banking, engineering, petroleum, government agencies, medical facilities, educational institutions, and airline industries.<br>
<br>
<STRONG>Session Information</STRONG><br>
General sessions are held each morning and are focused on subjects of interest to all attendees. In the afternoons, you may choose from a wide variety of breakout sessions and workshop sessions.
The breakout sessions are arranged in seven tracks: Managerial, Technical, Emergency Response, Communications, Strategic, Issues and Answers and Professional Certification. Hands-on workshops are held on Sunday and Tuesday afternoon. With such a wide variety, youre sure to find just the right information to fit your situation.<br>
<br>
<STRONG>Pricing Information</STRONG><br>
DRJs conference is the best value in the industry. Our prices have not increased since 1989. And this year, you get even more for your money. We are committed to providing the best information at the best price.  The Sunday workshops are free to all conference attendees.<br>
<br>
Speaker Information<br>
Weve selected an impressive array of experts from both the corporate and private sectors. Each speaker brings his own unique perspective to the conference, providing numerous learning opportunities for you.
The first day of the conference will kick off with two well-known figures in the world today. Brigadier General Steve Ritchie will lead off with an outstanding motivational presentation. The second session will feature James Lee Witt, director of the Federal Emergency Management Agency. Mr. Witt will provide us with new strategies to address the changing corporate contingency and public emergency management environments.
Additional general sessions will be led by industry leaders, Michael Mulholland. David Nolan, John Copenhaver,  Tari Schreider, and Ken Vander Wal. <br>
Our breakout sessions and workshops will feature expert speakers, who will share their extensive knowledge and experience.<br>
<br>

Location, Location, Location<br>
Our conference is situated along the beautiful San Diego Bay at the Sheraton San Diego Hotel & Marina. The site is just minutes from San Diego International Airport and is surrounded by numerous popular attractions. The hotel provides shuttle services, spacious ballrooms, exhibit areas, meeting rooms and numerous restaurants. In addition, there are spas, fitness rooms and two outdoor pools.<br>
<br>

Lunch, Exhibitor Information<br>
and Hospitality by Comdisco
Our popular roundtable discussions at lunch will continue this year. This allows those from the same industry to network during the lunch hour. In addition, this year lunch will be served upstairs each day. Dessert will be served downstairs in the exhibit hall, where some 90+ exhibitors will be displaying their products and services. Exhibitor prize drawings will be held Sunday, Monday & Tuesday. On Tuesday, Comdisco is hosting a conference hospitality at 6:30 p.m. to 8:30 p.m.   <br><br><Br>
<center>
