<img src="line.gif">
<br>
<center><font size=5><strong>The DRJ Now Accepts M/C and Visa For Quick and Easy Ordering!<br>
<img src="mc.gif" align=absmiddle>  or  <img src="visa.gif" align=absmiddle><br>Just Call (314) 894-0276 to Order or Fax to (314) 894-7474</center></font size></strong><br><br>
<img src="cone.gif"><font size=5><a href="order.html">Go to the Order Form<br></font size></a>
<img src="line.gif">
<font size=3>
<blockquote><p>
 You have been told, "You are the person who will be responsible for:  gathering a BIA together, write up a
 Business Contingency Plan, gathering Surveys about well known Vendors, gathering information about consultants."  But
 you don't know where to start.  Well let us be the first to introduce you to BIA AND BEYOND.  BIA AND BEYOND
 is the most talked about training Video to date.
<p>
Disaster Recovery Journal is debuting a series of training sessions on video which will act as a supplement for anyone interested in establishing or building upon a disaster recovery plan.
<p>
These innovative training tools will feature narration and information. The first video focuses on Business Impact Analysis and Beyond.  A workbook, especially designed for the video, will be included at no additional cost. This workbook will include all the forms necessary for gathering data and compiling a data analysis. Having the workbook provides easier understanding of the Business Impact Analysis.
<p>
Future topics will include Recovery Strategies, Plan Development,  Exercising the Plan, and other related subjects. All videos will include a workbook.
<p>
These videos provide an inexpensive, accessible way for all contingency planners to learn from an expert in the field. They are a must for anyone interested in furthering their disaster recovery knowledge. <P>
</blockquote><br>

