<title>Disaster Recovery Journal</title>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
<center><img src="drjlogo.gif"><font size=3><br>
<font size=4><i><B><STRONG>The Journal Dedicated to Business Continuity<br>
April, May, June 1996</STRONG></B></i><br></center>
<img src="line.gif"><br>
<br>

 
  
<font size=3>
<font size=6>1996 SURVEY: DISASTER RECOVERY SERVICES
<br></font>
<font size=4>Compilied by the Staff of the DRJ <br></font>
<br>
<br>





Disaster Recovery Journal  publishes three surveys on the subjects of alternative sites, PC software, and consultants. This survey focuses on companies who provide services other than those already published.
Disaster Recovery Journal does not in any way endorse these companies or their services. Vendors who are not included should call our office to be added to our list for future survey reports.<br>
<br>
Aeroscopic Engineers, Inc.<br>
Ian Spiszman<br>
5245 San Fernando Road - West<br>
Los Angeles, CA  90039<br>
(800) 950-2376, (213) 245-3024, fax (213) 245-3028<br>
<br>
Aeroscopic Engineers, Inc. has been in business since 1958, specializing in recovery operations. Aeroscopic has assisted over 12,000 companies, recovering firms from the effects of fires, floods, smoke and corrosion. The companys emergency "Demand Side" service program provides that key element which later allows for the decision-making, loss adjustment process to take place in a calm, controlled environment. Available 24-hours a day, Aeroscopics primary "Demand Side" services include a variety of services such as water removal, extraction of water, indoor smoke and malodor control; and asbestos sampling and analysis. Aeroscopic also offers post-emergency services. Their IAW division specializes in indoor air pollution control and the sales, rental and maintenance of particulate and gas purging IAQ systems. <br>
<br>
Aggreko, Inc.<br>
John Williamson<br>
4607 W. Admiral Doyle Drive<br>
New Iberia, LA  70560<br>
(318) 367-7884, fax (318) 367-0870<br>
<br>
Aggreko Inc. provides emergency utilities including silenced diesel generators (15kw to 2000kw), dehumidifiers (to 10,000 cfm), air conditioners (to 60 tons), air and water-cooled chillers (up to 1000 tons), electric heaters (20kw to 150kw) and all the auxiliary equipment to make up complete systems. The services are available 24 hours from over 30 North American depots. Corporate and emergency response plans available.<br>
<br>
Arcus Data Security, Inc.<br>
Lezlie Campeggi<br>
P.O. Box 326<br>
Union City, CA 94587<br>
(800) GO-ARCUS, fax (510) 471-9736<br>
<br>
Arcus Data Security, Inc. offers offsite data storage, emergency media movement, disaster recovery support services, temporary and contract labor support service, automated media management systems, bar code scanning systems and data products supplies, relocation of media libraries and other customized services from 23 vault facilities throughout the U.S. and one location in the U.K.<br>
<br>
AT&T/NCR Business Recovery Services<br>
Greg Hanson<br>
1611 S. Main St., SDC-3<br>
Dayton, OH 45479<br>
(800) 587-0911, fax (513) 449-2599<br>
<br>
AT&T/NCR Business Recovery Services offers work area recovery, hotsite backup and recovery - NCR equipment, disaster recovery planning software, and off-site data storage.<br>
<br>
Baseline Software, Inc.<br>
Michelle Jungsten<br>
P.O. Box 1219<br>
Sausalito, CA  94966<br>
(415) 332-7763, fax (415) 332-8032<br>
<br>
"Information Security Policies Made Easy" is a compilation of 730 already-written policies by internationally-known consultants. Save time developing policies for information security manuals, user training seminars, systems development standards, contingency plans, outsourcing agreements, and requests for proposals. Distributed in hardcopy and on disk (IBM-PC or MAC), this policy construction kit provides the most comprehensive collection of policies on the market. Contents include: how to get management support, how to write policies, mock-up initial policy statement, comprehensive list of info security standards, and reference materials. Policies cover passwords, access control, viruses, user privileges, intellectual property rights, contingency planning, user awareness, and more. Baseline Software Inc.s E-mail address is: Info@baselinesoft.com. Their Internet site is located at www.baselinesoft.com/people/infosec.<br>
<br>
Bear Computer Systems Inc.<br>
Maureen Kenney<br>
9584 Topanga Canyon Blvd.<br>
Chatsworth, CA  91311<br>
(818) 341-0403, fax (818) 341-1831<br>
<br>
Bear Computer Systems Inc. offers software for DEC VAX and HP-UX that provides automatic complete shadowing (mirroring) of transactions, across a network to a remote site of your choice. Completely transparent to user, it allows immediate recovery to full operations without loss of data. The companys e-mail address is: Bearcom@Bearcomp.com.<br>
<br>
Bell Atlantic<br>
Call for address of local office<br>
(800) 846-1200 ext. 999<br>
<br>
Bell Atlantics CommGuard Switched Redirect Service enables customer requirements to be met and proves quality service during a  disaster or an emergency. Bell Atlantics CommGuard FlexAlert Notification Service enables businesses and governments alike to respond quickly to an emergency, crisis or urgent business situation.<br>
