<br>
A SURVEY OF DISASTER RECOVERY CONSULTANTS<br>
<br>
<font size=2>The following information is a compilation of the results of a consultant survey conducted by Disaster Recovery Journal.  <br>
The Disaster Recovery Journal does not in any way endorse these companies or their services.  Vendors who are not included in this survey should call Disaster Recovery Journal at (314) 894-0276 to be added to our vendor list.  Those vendors will be included in future survey reports.<br>
<hr><br>
Advanced Information Management<br>
Allen Anderson<br>
12940 Harbor Drive<br>
Woodbridge, VA 22192<br>
(703) 643-1002 Fax (703) 643-2722<br>
<br>
In business for sixteen years, Advanced Information Management (A.I.M.)  has one location  and three full-time consultants.  They have been involved in or completed over 100 disaster recovery plans.  The firms focus is on data processing, LANs, business resumption and vulnerability.  The company provides complete disaster recovery plans, project management for disaster recovery planning and automated PC-based recovery.  A.I.M. also provides contracting in foreign countries.  The average hourly rate is $188; the average daily rate is $1,500 a day.<br>
<hr><br>
H. Allison & Associates, Inc.<br>
Herb Smyers<br>
3013 South Wolf Road, Suite 105<br>
Westchester, IL  60154<br>
(708) 784-1105 Fax (708) 993-3624<br>
<br>
In business for three years, H. Allison & Associates, Inc. has one location and three full-time consultants, who plan to be certified as CDRPs in 1996. They've been involved in or completed 42 disaster recovery plans. The firm's emphasis is on business continuity, data processing, corporate functions, emergency management and voice/data solutions. The company provides fully documented disaster recovery and business continuity plans, an automated PC-based recovery plan, and contracting in foreign countries. The average hourly rate is $187.50.<br>
<hr><br>
Archive Management, Inc.<br>
Carole A. Gudde<br>
6455 Box Springs Blvd.<br>
Riverside, CA  92507<br>
(909) 656-2238, (800) 660-2724 (CA only)<br>
Fax (909) 656-2520<br>
<br>
In business for five years, Archive Management Inc. has one location and one full-time consultant. They've been involved in or completed several disaster recovery plans. The firm's emphasis is on forms, records, tapes, cartridge, container and evidence protection. The company provides assistance and direction for  disaster recovery and business continuity plans and contracting in foreign countries. The average hourly rate is $50.00 plus expenses.<br>
<hr><br>
