David Sarabacha<br>
Spear Street Tower, One Market Plaza<br>
San Francisco, CA  94109<br>
(415) 281-1144, (415) 546-8600<br>
Fax (415) 543-1827<br>
<br>
In business for 10 years, Arthur Andersen LLP has offices worldwide with approximately 500 employees, some of which are CDRPs. They've been involved in or completed approximately 100 disaster recovery plans. The firm's emphasis is on all functional and support areas of business continuity planning. The company provides complete services from project initiation to plan maintenance and approval. An automated PC-based recovery plan, and contracting in foreign countries are also provided. The average hourly rate is $120 -$150.<br>
<hr><br>
Bellcore<br>
Mr. Norm Meier, Jr. CDRP<br>
3 Corporate Place<br>
Rm PYA 2J-231<br>
Piscataway, NJ 08854-4199<br>
(908) 699-4367, or 1-800-830-HELP<br>
On the Web- http://www.bellcore.com<br>
<br>
Bellcore's Disaster Management Services provides consulting in business continuity planning/ management, recovery planning, disaster site management, and recovery from man-made or natural disasters.  As communications disaster experts serving the "Baby Bells" since 1984, we can assist you at the disaster site with: root cause analysis, restoration guidelines, and recovery management.  In addition, we work with you to develop proactive planning and environmental strategies to avoid or deal with future disasters.  The objectives of Disaster Management services are: minimize downtime; minimize the recurrence of disasters; provide cost-effective business solutions. <br>
<hr><br>
+Borzy Consulting Inc.<br>
Ralph Borzyczkowski<br>
