<BR>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><B>MIDWEST CONTINGENCY PLANNERS, INC.<BR>
GROUP MEETING DECEMBER 10, 1996<BR>
(Community Hospital North)</CENTER></B></FONT><BR>
<BR>
<B>CALL TO ORDER - PRESIDENT</B><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
The meeting was called to order at 1:30 P.M. by the president Gary Wyne.  Gary welcomed everyone and reminded Members to verify their information on the Membership List, and initial it, in the Red Book.  He also requested that Guests sign-the Guest Register  in the Blue Book.  Gary also mentioned the various material laid out on the table.  He also pointed to the refreshments available for today's meeting.  And requested that everyone complete the Evaluation Form regarding today's session.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>GRATITUDE TO HOST - PRESIDENT</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
Gary thanked Jerry Green, Community Hospital North, and Verna Henry, Community Hospital East for hosting today's meeting. 
<BR>
<STRONG>INTRODUCTIONS - PRESIDENT</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
Gary had new attendees introduce themselves, the company they represent, then had everyone else in the room introduce themselves too. <BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>OPEN BUSINESS MEETING - PRESIDENT</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
The business meeting was opened with a reminder that only one (1) member from a Member Company is authorized to vote on business matters.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>APPROVAL OF PRIOR MEETING MINUTES - SECRETARY</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
The minutes of the October  8, 1996 meeting were approved as written.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>MEMBERSHIP - SECRETARY</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
Two (2) new Member Companies joined MCP, Lantech of  America, and The American Legion, giving a new membership count of 49.
<BR>
These new companies were welcomed to MCP, and awarded Certificates for joining.  <BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>COMMITTEE REPORTS</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
None.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>ANNOUNCEMENTS & COMMUNICATIONS  - PRESIDENT </STRONG>(IN ABSENCE OF THE VICE PRESIDENT)<BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
Future meeting are:<BR>
February 11, 1997 at Conseco Companies, 11815 N. Pennsylvannia AV., Carmel, IN 46032<BR>
April  8, 1997 at Citizens Gas & Coke Utility, 2020 N. Meridian St., Indianapolis, IN 46202<BR>
June 10, 1997.<BR>
<BR>
Gary received favorable feedback on repeating the Disaster Recovery Workshop.  The Board will pursue the planning of it.
<BR>
A page showing Positions Wanted and Upcoming Events from the Disaster Recovery Journal (DRJ) magazine were displayed.
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>UNFINISHED BUSINESS</STRONG> <BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - <BR>
Bylaws  - President<BR>
The revised Bylaws have been approved by the State of Indiana.  Member Company representative were told to see the Secretary, after the meeting, to receive and sign for their copy. <BR>
<BR>
Salary Survey results  - Paul Jansen, USA Group<BR>
The tabulated results will be available at the next meeting.  Contact me if you are still interested in participating in it.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>MISCELLANEOUS BUSINESS</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - <BR>
The Secretary announced that whomever has the two (2) Disaster Recovery videos (Volume I and II) , to please return them.<BR>
<BR>
The President field questions from the audience, and generated conversation on topics, such as:<BR>
  <dd>       - Data Synchronization among multi -platforms<BR>
     <dd>      - Where does one start to build a disaster recovery plan<BR>
   <dd>      - How does one involve Human Resource in the planning, and how is it budgeted<BR>
    <dd>      - How to create an Application Priority Restoration List<BR>
<BR>
The consensus is the notification of the meetings are being received in a timely manner.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>NEW BUSINESS</STRONG> <BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - --<BR>
Chris Rosendall, IBM/BRS volunteered to be the Chairman of the 1997 - 98 Nominating Committee.  Contact him at (219) 460-4221 if you would like to serve on this committee.  Voting will take place in June 1997.<BR>
<BR>
 Ed Jacques, Conseco volunteered to be the Chairman of the Audit Committee.  Members interested in contributing to the organization can contact Ed at (317) 817-6216 to assist in the audit.  The audit report is due in April 1997.<BR>
<BR>
Past President, Sam Brummett has an new e -mail address:  sam.j. brummett@allison.com<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>FINANCIAL STATEMENT -TREASURER</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
The report was approved as presented.  <BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>CLOSE BUSINESS MEETING  - PRESIDENT</STRONG><BR>
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
With no other business items, the business session was formally closed.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>PROGRAM</STRONG><BR>
 - - - - - - - - - -<BR>
Part I  - Dave Perkins, Director, Operations Division, State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) gave an excellent presentation about his direct involvement of the International Eagle Flight #4184 that crashed in Roselawn, Indiana.  It was accompanied by graphic 'no-hold-barred' slides that left no survivors.<BR>
<BR>
He pointed some procedural things that were done wrong, and have since been corrected.   The interaction with the local fire department, local law enforcement agencies, the Federal Bureau of Investigation, the National Guard, Highway Department, etc., was amazing.  And the stress on the recovery personnel was above any normal level.  I can only say, if you missed this presentation, you missed a real life situation.<BR>
<BR>
Part II  -  Alden Taylor, Director of Public Affairs, SEMA discussed his role assisting local sites with public information activities.  His slide presentation included which agency has control over a disaster event,  the cascade ripple effect from a disaster, emergency planning ideas, etc.  He also shed some light on how individuals and small business can obtain financial assistance   SEMA's role is to get resources to the disaster site; they do not take control of the disaster recovery efforts.  He provided some valuable information to include in your Disaster/Recovery Plan too.<BR>
<BR>
The meeting was adjourned at 3:45 PM.<BR>
<BR>
       Respectfully submitted by,<BR>
<BR>
       Dick Pigati<BR>
       Secretary<BR>
       December 15, 1996<BR>




<br>
       




     
